(68723, 201854, 0, 1, 'Waltzing With The Keres/Don''t Go To The Water (Interlude)', '', '2010-04-20 00:00:00', 2010, 19, 1, 5, ' 	\nStepping off the train that night\nThe rain pours down from skies above\nJohn is singing in the background\nAbout all the things we do for love\nAnd all this seems just so surreal\nLike an image on the silver screen\nI''m reminded of my youthful days\nWhen I still believed in all those things\n\nBut then I see a girl come gliding down the street\nDance with me\nYou''ll be free\nLove me\nMy friend\nDance with me\nYou''ll be free\n\nJust before the break of dawn\nWith swollen eyes and frozen heart\nI am standing at the window sill\nPressed against the glass before me\nDiscerning shapes inside the heavy fog\nLike valkyries with outstretched claws\nI am wondering when they will come for me\n\nThen I see an arm come stretching out the mist\nDance with me\nYou''ll be free\nLove me\nMy friend\nDance with me\nYou''ll be free\n\nAnd we dance\n\nThis temple that you built for me\nSo fragile in its outer layers\nGlistens bright for all of those who see\nAs the insides fall to disrepair\nThe paint is peeling off the walls\nThe floors they crack as columns fall\nI am content to watch it all crash down around me\n\nThen I hear a voice come calling down the hall\nDance with me\nYou''ll be free\nLove me\nMy friend\nDance with me\nYou''ll be free\n\nThis book I read so long ago\nNow vacant in my present mind\nI am wondering where my soul goes\nWhen I choose to leave this world behind\nWill I reach that sea black\nIn the silence of oblivion\nOr will I burn inside a pit of hell\nAs the devil smiles upon me\n\nBut then I hear that voice come slicing through my mind\nDance with me\nYou''ll be free\nLove me\nMy friend\nDance with me\nYou''ll be free', '', 403, '', 'Ty Cooper & Andrew Rogers', 'Ty Cooper', 'Andrew Rogers & Ty Cooper', 'None', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-12-02 01:07:09', '2015-03-12 14:03:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(68724, 201854, 0, 1, 'Of Martyrs And Maenads', '', '2010-04-20 00:00:00', 2010, 19, 1, 5, 'It''s been 4 long years since I last saw your face\nStill a devil in disguise an angel in disgrace\nPassing me off like some poor soul to fix\nAnother project of yours its so horribly sick\nYou see being present don''t make you a saint\nYou feign eagerness and oh God it''s so quaint\nHow you stare at me with those innocent eyes\nWhile you''re firey tongue spits forth all your lies\n\nAnd I know that it''s all in my head\nBut I want to burn the world girl I''ll burn you instead\n\n''Cause I''m cold and I''m cruel\nI''m a passionless fool\nAnd I won''t let up til the world suffers too\nYou keep me around\nYet you hate when I''m down\nWell grab hold of my hand girl we''re all going down\n\n\nI''m not looking for bright skies I want them all pale\nWith flesh-stripping winds and hundred pound hail\nAnd deep sinking darkness to make me feel small\nTo take my inhibitions and shatter them all\nSo fire up the engines, the blue and red lights\nIts gonna be a party, one hell of a night!\nThe greatest of shows, thats been brewing for months\nSo please bring a guest boys it''ll only play once\n\nAnd I know that I''m raising my voice\nBut I want to kill the world girl I''ve got no choice\n\n''Cause I''m cold and I''m cruel\nI''m a passionless fool\nAnd I won''t give up til you all suffer too\nYou jerk me around\nThen you hate that I''m down\nWell grab to my hand girl this ships going down\n\nI wanna tear myself down to a ghost of a man\nTo match the destruction thats been dealt by my hand\nSo set back relax and understand\nThat if we don''t make it out alive it was part of the plan\n\nSo run to the doorway and please pass on through\nYou''re next in line girl don''t hold up the queue\nA supporting cast of thousands and you''re one of them too\nDo your job well or else we''ll replace all of you\nWith your candy cane smiles and barbie doll hair\nAnd your light-hearted manners so sweet and debonaire\nYou''ve lived this so long that you''re too blind to see\nYou''ve hardly faith for yourself, so why save some for me?\n\nAnd I know that I''m doing my best\nBut I can plainly see that you''re not that impressed\n\n''Cause I''m cold and I''m cruel\nI''m a passionless fool\nAnd I won''t give up til you all suffer too\nYou pass me around\n''Cause you hate when I''m down\nWell grab to my hand girls we''re all gonna drown', '', 272, '', 'Ty Cooper & Andrew Rogers', 'Ty Cooper', 'Andrew Rogers & Ty Cooper', 'None', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-12-02 01:08:48', '2015-03-12 14:03:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(68725, 201854, 0, 1, 'The Message', '', '2010-04-20 00:00:00', 2010, 19, 1, 5, 'And when the sun sets over Rogers\nDo you still remember what it was like\nWhen we wished it would never rise?\nThis vacancy that spans your bedside\nDo you still remember what it was like\nWhen I was there to hold you tight?\n\nAll this time, it passed us by\n\nDriving down from Kansas city\nWe held eachother''s hands for the first time\nAnd we held them the whole ride.\nIn the woods behind your bedroom\nBeneath the stars above we were as one\nTwo children so in love\n\nAll this time, it passed us by\n\nAs we set sail through open waters\nCould you see it ending like it did?\nAnd would you do it all again?\nA message lost like misread novels\nHinging on the tips of so few words\nOft spoke but never heard\n\nOh my god, what have we done?\n\nSo I''m sending out a signal\nA message in a bottle\nCarried on the radio waves to somewhere far away\n\nAnd when our bodies fade away\nThe earth has reached its final day\nAll of us that will remain, are the memories that I''ve laid', '', 226, '', 'Ty Cooper', 'Ty Cooper', 'Andrew Rogers & Ty Cooper', 'None', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-12-02 01:09:57', '2015-03-12 14:03:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
